02/04/2010
LONDON, United Kingdom -- A Croatian Serb arrested by British police for alleged war crimes will remain in custody pending extradition to Croatia, media reported on Thursday (April 1st).
Mile Bosnic was arrested on March 25th in Gloucester, based on an international arrest warrant issued by Croatia.
Zagreb has requested his extradition.
Bosnic allegedly committed war crimes against Croat civilians early in the 1991-1995 war in Croatia.
(BBC, Tanjug, Srna - 01/04/10)
